'''Al-Fotuwa Sports Club''' ({{lang-ar|نادي الفتوة الرياضي}}) is a [[Syria]]n football club based in [[Deir ez-Zor]], [[Syria]].

==History==
The club was founded in 1930 as Ghazi Club and 1950 renamed in Al Fotuwa Sports Club.<ref>[http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/club-profile/syria/al-fotuwa-sc/16607/ Al Fotuwa SC&nbsp;– Weltfussballarchiv]</ref>

==Achievements==
*'''[[Syrian League]]: 2'''
::Champion : 1990, 1991

*'''[[Syrian Cup]]: 4'''
::Winner : 1988, 1989, 1990, 1991

==Performance in AFC competitions==
*'''[[Asian Club Championship]]: 1 appearance'''
::[[Asian Club Championship 1989|1989]]: Qualifying Stage

