{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Amateur Softball Association of the Philippines |abbrev = ASAPHIL |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Softball]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = {{Start date|}} |aff = [[International Softball Federation]] |affdate = |region = |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Pasay]] |location = |president = [[Jean Henri Lhuillier]] |secretary = |url = |countryflag = Philippines |more = }}
The '''Amateur Softball Association of the Philippines''' is the national [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for [[softball]] in the [[Philippines]]. It is accredited by the [[International Softball Federation]] which is the governing body for the sport of softball in the world. It currently manages the men's and women's national teams for softball, the Blu Boys and Blu Girls.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/sports/2015/12/11/1531374/hs-collegiate-womens-softball-2-venues|title=HS, collegiate women’s softball up in 2 venues|publisher=Philstar|accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>
==External links== *[http://www.asaphil.com.ph Official Website] *[https://web.archive.org/web/20141003045529/http://olympic.ph/nsa_softball.html Amateur Softball Association of the Philippines profile at the Philippine Olympic Committee website]
