'''Esbjerg Stadionhal''' was an [[indoor arena]] located in [[Esbjerg]], [[Denmark]]. It opened in 1968 and had a capacity of 2,100 people. Its primary tenant was [[Team Esbjerg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stadions.dk/haller/esbjergsthal.asp |title=Esbjerg Stadionhal |publisher=Stadions.dk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teamesbjerg.dk/ |title=Team Esbjerg |publisher=Teamesbjerg.dk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sepe.dk/Default.aspx?ID=2057 |title=Idrætsparken |publisher=Sepe.dk |date= |accessdate=2014-06-01}}</ref> It also hosted non-sporting events such as exhibitions, fairs and concerts. In 2012 it was replaced by [[Blue Water Dokken]].
