{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Estádio Da Liga Muçulmana | nickname = | image = | fullname = Estádio Da Liga Muçulmana | location = [[Matola]], [[Mozambique]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Liga Muçulmana de Maputo]] | seating_capacity = 5,000 | }} '''Estádio Da Liga Muçulmana''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Matola]], [[Mozambique]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, on club level by [[Liga Muçulmana de Maputo]] of the [[Moçambola]]. The stadium has a capacity of 5,000 spectators.<ref>https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2011/02/12/africa/caf-champions-league/liga-muculmana-de-maputo/zesco-united/1059586/venue/</ref>
