{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Royal Military Academy Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = Royal Military College cricket grounds, Sandhurst, Camberley, Surrey, England, ca. 1895.jpg | location = [[Sandhurst, Berkshire]], near [[Camberley]], [[Surrey]] | establishment = 1893 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1938 | club1 = [[British Army cricket team|Army]] | date = 28 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/372.html Ground profile }}
'''Royal Military Academy Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Sandhurst, Berkshire]] near [[Camberley]], [[Surrey]]. The ground itself is located within the grounds of the [[Royal Military Academy Sandhurst|Royal Military Academy]] at Sandhurst. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1893, when Royal Military Academy Sandhurst played Dr Nicholson's XI.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/372_misc.html Other matches played on Royal Military Academy Ground]</ref> In use constantly since 1893, it hosted its only [[first-class cricket|first-class]] match in 1938, when the [[British Army cricket team|British Army]] played [[Oxford University Cricket Club|Oxford University]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/372_f.html First-Class Matches played on Royal Military Academy Ground]</ref> More recently, in 2006 the ground played host to a match between Officer Cadets of the Royal Military Academy and the [[Afghanistan national cricket team]] on their first tour to [[England]].<ref>[http://www.cricinfo.com/england/content/story/250526.html Afghans on parade at Sandhurst]</ref>
